DOMAIN 4/6: QUANTUM HALL EFFECT
  (connects Berry phase to Chern-Simons to metrology)

  R_K = h/e² = 25812.80745 Ω (exact)
  R_K = 1/α × (h/2πe²) × 2π = 1/α × R_quantum
  R_K = 2π/(α × 2π × ... ) ... let me compute this properly:

  α = e²/(4πε₀ℏc) = 1/137.035999177
  R_K = h/e² = 2πℏ/e² = (2π/α) × (ℏc × 4πε₀/e²) ...
  Simply: R_K × (e²/(2πℏ)) = 1, and α = e²/(4πε₀ℏc)
  So R_K = (2π)/(α × 4πε₀c) = (2π)/(α × ...)

  The QHE MEASURED value of R_K before it became exact:
  R_K = 25812.80745... Ω gave α⁻¹ = 137.0359991...
  This was a measurement of α through the QHE.

