DOMAIN 5: REAL BAND GAPS (material data)

  Material   E_gap (eV)      E_gap/m_e
  Si              1.120   2.191785e-06
  Ge              0.670   1.311157e-06
  GaAs            1.420   2.778871e-06
  InP             1.350   2.641884e-06
  GaN             3.400   6.653634e-06
  SiC             3.260   6.379661e-06
  Diamond         5.470   1.070452e-05

  These ratios depend on:
    - α (Coulomb interaction between electrons and nuclei)
    - Nuclear charges Z (integers)
    - Crystal structure (integers: coordination numbers)
    - Effective masses (depend on α and Z)

  Band gaps are NOT SM free parameters — they are derived
  quantities from α + nuclear physics + crystal geometry.
  Testing them against the basis would be testing whether
  DERIVED quantities (not free parameters) have structure.
  This is a different question from parameter reduction.

