DOMAIN 9: JOSEPHSON JUNCTION DATA

  K_J = 2e/h = 483597848400000.0 Hz/V (exact)

  Shapiro step at 10 GHz: V_1 = 20.6783 μV
  This is exact — no free parameters.

  Nb superconducting gap: Δ = 1.5 meV
  Nb T_c = 9.26 K
  Δ/(k_B T_c) = 1.8798
  BCS prediction: π/e^γ = 1.7639
  (where γ = Euler-Mascheroni constant)

  The BCS gap ratio π/e^γ = 1.7639... is a DERIVED quantity
  from the BCS theory. It involves π (= 4R₂) and the
  Euler-Mascheroni constant γ = 0.5772...

  Nb's deviation from BCS: strong coupling effects.
  This is material physics, not SM parameter physics.

