WHAT DOMAIN DATA COULD WE TEST?
===========================================================================

HIGH-PRECISION DIMENSIONLESS RATIOS FROM DOMAIN DATA:

  1. Hydrogen Lamb shift / Rydberg energy ~ 2.5e-7
     Theory: contains α⁵ ln(α), known QED coefficients
     → The QED coefficients contain ζ(3), ζ(5), π², ln(2)
     → These are EXACTLY our transcendental basis!

  2. Hydrogen HFS / Rydberg energy ~ 4.3e-7
     Theory: contains α²(m_e/m_p), known QED corrections
     → Same transcendental basis in the corrections

  3. BCS gap ratio Δ/(k_B T_c) ~ 1.764
     Theory: = π/e^γ exactly in weak-coupling BCS
     → This IS a transcendental prediction (π and γ)

  4. FQHE energy gaps (material-dependent)
     → Depend on α, B, m* — not new free parameters

  KEY INSIGHT:
  The domain data that involves our transcendental basis
  is the QED CORRECTIONS to hydrogen levels.
  These corrections are COMPUTED from α using perturbative
  series with coefficients containing ζ(3), ζ(5), π², ln(2).

  But this is exactly what PHYS-9 already did —
  the QED series for a_e, inverted to get α.
  The hydrogen Lamb shift is the SAME physics (QED)
  applied to a DIFFERENT observable (energy levels vs g-2).

  We are not missing a data source.
  We are missing a PRINCIPLE that determines the parameters.

  